{"TopicId":34607,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Crowd-sourced experiment to measure the SIZE OF THE EARTH","CreatedByName":"technicalfool","CreatedById":70430,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-24T18:23:54Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"technicalfool","CreatedById":70430,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-24T18:23:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ll let that infamous Youtube firebrand Thunderf00t explain it:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/HX-UtuZeysM?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIf anybody is interested, you basically need a stick, a ruler and a camera. A smartphone or tablet with a time-lapse app would be even better.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PakledHostage","CreatedById":8059,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-24T18:59:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe late, great, Carl Sagan describing how Eratosthenes calculated the size of the Earth in about 200 BC. Just how accurate his estimate was is a topic of debate, but it was certainly better than Ptolomy\u0027s later estimate of about 29000 km.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022459\u0022 height=\u0022344\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/0JHEqBLG650?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-06-24T19:06:24Z\u0022 title=\u002206/24/2013 07:06  PM\u